	<p>I too will never understand the Macs suck argument.  I don't like windows because of the unnecessary complication involved with it compared to OS X.  But I use windows and don't claim it to suck just not the preference given a choice.  However, system 9 wasn't exactly superseding windows in any meaningful way either.  I think it was less stable in many ways than windows 98 se or millenium.  (I got back into macs with the introduction of OS X)<br />
<br />
That being said I remember having a DEC Rainbow 100 B and a Fat Mac at the same time.  For everyday tasks guess which got used more?<br />
<br />
IMHO Apple has always been innovative and a market leader in innovation they just have no follow through and lack a decent "well that was successful now let's take advantage of the success" plan.  Too busy trying give their shareholders short term profit.</p>
	
	
	
